snippet.textDisplay:
This is sadly very possible. Even with a concussion, any frontal lobe damage could do this. The frontal lobe is responsible for personality and impulse control.

And the mother being submissive to the father would not be due to the pills. The mother is likely having a big struggle. She loved this man and married him. It must have been very traumatic for her.

The medication given to the mom could have been prescribed to him and he had her take it. It also could have been over the counter sedatives or something bought on the street.

Is this likely, no. Is it possible, sadly. The mother's response is a classic abuse response. Very upsetting.
